1. Write the equation of tangent line to function

f(x) = 5 * sin (e^2x + pi/2)
x0 = 1/2

Answer

g(x) = f(x0) + f'(x0)*(x-x0)

f(x0) = f(1/2) = 5 * sin (e + pi/2) = -4.56

f'(x) = 5 (cos(e^2x)' = 5*(cos(e^2x))'(e^2x)' = -10 * sin(e^2x) * e^2x

f'(x0) = -10 * sin(e) * e = -11.17

x - x0 = x - 1/2

g(x) = 5 * sin (e + pi/2) - 10 * sin(e) * e * (x - 1/2) = 5 * sin (e + pi/2) - 10 * sin(e) * e * x - 5 * sin(e) * e = -10.14 - 11.17x 
Answer is g (x) = -10.14 - 11.17x  
